[Student "S"]
{With opening hand and 4-card \S support this is an ideal Jacoby 2NT response. Partner says 3NT.  

North has some extra strength and a 5-card \S suit. This is the point in the bidding where you would make a control bid, showing an Ace. Well, you would if you actually had an Ace. The way you indicate your lack of a control is to just return the the agreed trump suit. So you bid 4\S and partner passes.}

